::::::::::::How to install “Avro” in Ubuntu 17.10:::::::::::::::100% working.
Step 1::
$ sudo apt-get install gjs gir1.2-ibus-1.0 libibus-1.0-5 libibus-1.0-dev ibus-gtk ibus-gtk3 ibus-clutter ibus-qt4

2.it will take some time for install those required files. then again run this command
$ wget "https://github.com/maateen/avro/releases/download/v2.1/avro_2.1-3_all.deb"

& finally run this command:::
$ sudo dpkg -i avro_2.1-3_all.deb

I hope, all is well now and the installation has been finished.

and restart your computer.

and then.........
 1st. go to settings +Region & language +input sources then+ click (+) button +select bangla(bangladesh) +and search bengali(Avro phonetic)  

end end end
 
